message: /* Shmuley Boteach */
Removed false information, added information about his current organization, without adding promotions.
/* January 2021 */
added a section about Boteach's current organization, The World Values Network, with citations from various sources about the work that is done by the organization.

Removed discrepancies, fixed grammatical errors. The article from fox news is said by Rabbi Shmuley to be false, and that the source that the writer used for his 2001 article is not credible. There is a lot of fake news on the internet, but Wikipedia should not be publishing these fake stories considering there is only one source saying that this information is true.
/* Shmuley Boteach edits */
Removed the section about infant circumcision. Rabbi Shmuley denies being in favor of infant mutilation, and he deems these claims to be false.

I removed libel from this page. Including the false information that Rabbi Shmuley Boteach dipped into his charity funds to pay for a house. This is libel, and if it is put back up again, he is considering taking legal action against the editor of this page.
Removed discrepancies, fixed grammatical errors.
Removed False information about discrepancies about his charity.

/* Michael Jackson */ Removed as the source, Roger Friedman, was fired by Fox News, who wrote of him "Roger Friedman’s views in no way reflect the views of News Corporation." https://deadline.com/2009/04/exclusive-fox-news-fires-showbiz-columnist-for-encouraging-piracy-8996/

Removed section as Boteach never served as Rabbi in Willesden. Removed section as Roger Friedman was fired by Fox News and is not a credible source. April 4th 2009 Fox said of Friedman "Roger Friedman’s views in no way reflect the views of News Corporation."
Added that he is most famous Rabbi in America, as quoted in Washington Post.
